      "content": "Well, industry skeptics often say that heavy regulation may stifle innovation, hindering technological advancement and giving a competitive edge to entities in regions with looser regulations. They argue that such proactiveness could inadvertently support less scrupulous actors who operate outside of strict European standards. The existential threat as they see it is not posed by the technology itself, but by the loss of global competitive advantage and potential forfeiture of leadership in the new AI-powered age. They prefer a more measured, self-regulation approach or international consensus on standards.",
